result.execSummary:
The defendant Dylan S. Nyman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:38 am case called. Defendant Dylan S. Nyman in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on the record.     Complaint Stated.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.      Defendant advised of permissible punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:No Contest to Count 1 & Count 2.   Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Court dismisses repeater enhancer on each count. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 1 year. Concurrent to each other but Consecutive to any other sentence including but not limited to Waupaca County case 15CF355. CONDITIONS: Restitution of $110.00. No Contact with Larsen Cooperative in Wild Rose. Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court. Defendant to complete ID.   Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given.
